{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> περι-σχίζω</b>, <br /> <b>slit and tear off</b>, ἐσθῆτα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Cicero” 36, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “DMeretr.” 8.1; κιτῶνα “BGU” 22.16 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; <b>slit open</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 550a30 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, π. τῷ μετώπῳ κόμη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 2.25. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, of a river, περισχίζεσθαι τὸν χῶρον <b>to split round</b> a piece of land, i.e. <b>divide into two branches and surround</b> it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.51; π. περὶ τὸ χωρίον 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 3.42.7, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, of a stream of men, <b>part and go different ways</b>, περιεσχίζοντο ἔνθεν καὶ ἔνθεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 315b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of light, αὐγὴ πολλαχοῦ π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.407e, compare 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Igne” 52 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of sound, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 2.116. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>strip of all his clothes</b>, τινα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Epicteti Dissertationes” 1.25.30. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8765","accentedUnicode":"περισχίζω","shortDef":"to split","mediumDef":"to split","stepGloss":"to split","stepTransliteration":"perischizō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}